OL,6,FMonths earlier, in August, police were
OL,7,Fcalled to an incident where Gillan was
OL,8,Freportedly drunk and making threats.
OL,9,FUpon police arrival, Gillan was said
OL,10,Fto be aggressive and threw a series of
OL,11,Fpunches at four police officers.
OL,13,FGillan was jailed for five years and
OL,14,Fwas handed an additional two-year
OL,15,Fextension to his licence period.
OL,17,FDetective Constable Matthew Owens,
OL,18,FCumberland CID, said: "Gillan is a
OL,19,Fdangerous individual who put lives at
OL,20,Frisk when setting fire to a car in the
OL,21,Fearly hours of a morning.
